    "The answers were brief, and the knowledge graph captures a network of correct linkages between the coastal ecosystems to carbon storage as well as protection from storms and erosion.",
    "It also suggests that the protection and restoration of coastal ecosystems are linked to blue carbon solutions (finance mechanisms).",
    "The specific prompt provided one general reference to a seminal paper in which the conservation and restoration of mangroves, salt marshes, and seagrasses are seen as critical in mitigating climate change [35].Figure 5 shows the knowledge graph related to the question, How can local and indigenous knowledge be integrated into coastal management practices?",
    "The response, while adequate, did not go into great depth, demonstrating how traditional knowledge and practices can lead to more sustainable and culturally appropriate management practices.",
    "This lack of depth may be due to scarce interdisciplinary literature sources."
